# --- Vercel (production / preview) ---
# Add secrets in the Vercel dashboard: Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# Do not put API keys in the static page or in git.

# --- Auth (recommended for Vercel) — when AUTH_SESSION_SECRET is set, /login.html is required and APIs need the cookie.
# Generate secret: openssl rand -hex 32
# AUTH_EMAIL=
# AUTH_PASSWORD=
# AUTH_SESSION_SECRET=

# Used by /api/* (see api/*.js). Set in Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables for production.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=          # api/extract.js — Chat Completions + JSON schema (gpt-4o-mini class models)
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini # optional; must support response_format json_schema
# SHAPE_API_KEY=           # or SHAPE_ACCESS_TOKEN — Authorization header (full token string)
# SHAPE_CRM_ID=20931      # required for search: POST /search/lead/{SHAPE_CRM_ID}
# SHAPE_BASE_URL=https://secure-api.setshape.com/api   # optional override

# --- Local ---
# Copy to .env for local `npm run dev` (dev-server.cjs) or `vercel dev`. Keep .env gitignored. One VAR=value per line.
